# Local dev notes (copy to dev.local.md)

Copy this file once:

```bash
cp dev.local.md.example dev.local.md
```

Fill in your real values. `dev.local.md` is gitignored — safe for passwords.

---

## Test / dev logins (TableTap UI)

| Account | Email | Password |
|---------|-------|----------|
| Test 1 | test1@test.com | _(fill in — you chose at register)_ |
| Test 2 | test2@test.com | _(fill in — you chose at register)_ |

Registered via http://localhost:5173/register — not seeded in SQL.

To list accounts in pgAdmin:

```sql
SELECT id, email, created_at FROM users ORDER BY created_at;
```

---

## Quick start after a break

```bash
npm run dev
```

- App: http://localhost:5173
- API: http://localhost:3001
- Health: http://localhost:3001/api/health

---

## Environment

- Secrets live in `server/.env` (copy from `server/.env.example`)
- Do not commit `server/.env`

| Variable | Your notes |
|----------|------------|
| DATABASE_URL | (remote pgAdmin host or `postgresql://cardinv:cardinv@localhost:5432/card_inventory`) |
| JWT_SECRET | |
| CLIENT_URL | http://localhost:5173 |

